[6] Czech Republic
Date: Tue 17 Apr 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/czech-republic-measles-increase-due-insufficient-vaccination-37891/


Health officials in the Czech Republic are reporting an increase in measles cases so far in 2018. For the 1st 2 months of the year [2018], 29 cases have been reported, according to a local media report (computer translated).

Principal hygienist Eva Gottvald explains that there are 23 infected patients in Prague, 5 in the Liberec region, and 1 in Pardubice. Half the cases were imported from Ukraine. The reason for the spread is insufficient vaccination.

How contagious is measles? Answer: Very

Once you've had measles, your body builds up resistance (immunity) to the virus and it's highly unlikely you'll get it again.

However, measles can lead to serious and potentially life-threatening complications in some people. These include infections of the lungs (pneumonia) and brain (encephalitis).

