[7] Serbia
Date: Tue 17 Apr 2018
Source: The Silver Telegram [edited]
https://sivtelegram.media/the-measles-outbreak-in-serbia-more-than-4-5-thousand-people-were-ill-15-died/5863/


In Serbia, the number of victims of epidemic of measles has reached 15 people, from the beginning of the epidemic in the fall of 2017. The total number of cases is 4740, according to the representative of the Institute of public health of Serbia.

"Of 4740 cases, 15 people died, and 500 patients developed serious complications, including pneumonia and brain inflammation. In this case, it is difficult to predict, however in recent days there is a decrease in the number of infected that is on the one hand due to the success of immunization [and on the other the] warm time of the year when more people are outdoors," said the doctor.

The physician also noted that the measures taken have had some effect -- the number of vaccinated people in age from 12 months-14 years increased to 94 percent.

The epidemic began in the territory of Kosovo and Metohija, but in December [2017] the number of cases in Central Serbia for the 1st time exceeded the number of patients in this Autonomous region.

[Byline: Jan Hartman]

