[8] Kansas
Date: Mon 16 Apr 2018 4:21 PM CDT
Source: KSHB/41 Action News [edited]
https://www.kshb.com/news/local-news/measles-cases-continue-to-grow-in-eastern-kansas-outbreak


The measles outbreak in eastern Kansas continues to grow with 16 cases now reported in 3 counties.

According to the Kansas Department of Health and Environment (KDHE), 13 cases have been reported in Johnson county, 2 in Linn county, and one in Miami county since 8 Mar 2018.

KDHE does not believe this outbreak is linked to the 2 cases reported in Missouri.

